               <history>
                  <origin>Completed by <persName role="scr" key="person_f7840">ʿAbd al-Ghanī ibn
                        ʿAbd al-Wahhāb</persName>, probably in the <origPlace cert="medium"
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208" key="place_7000208">Indian
                        subcontinent</origPlace>
                     <origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1607-09" to="1607-10">Jumādá II 1016
                        AH (Sep.–Oct. 1607 CE)</origDate></origin>
                  <provenance><p>Subsequently owned by Chetham Librarian <persName role="fmo"
                           key="person_92189357" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/92189357">John Haddon
                           Hindley (1765–1827)</persName>, after whose death, the volume sold for £2
                        12 shillings to Hall . by the <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7011781" key="place_7011781"
                           >London</placeName> firm of <persName role="bsl"
                           key="person_1555163159917201640001"
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/1555163159917201640001/">Howell and
                           Stewart</persName> sold many of his manuscripts. Note that although
                           <persName key="person_f7838">Siavash Rafiee-Rad</persName> implies that
                        Samuel Robinson of Wilmslow formerly owned this manuscript, neither external
                        nor internal evidence to suggest this.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Unknown. Probably transferred from the University of Manchester Library to
                        the <orgName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/312795145/#John_Rylands_Library">John
                           Rylands Library</orgName> after the institutions merged in <date
                           calendar="#Gregorian" when="1972">1972</date>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
